What is a SERVER?
A server is a software or physical device that hosts information requested by a client-side software eg web browser

Role of the Domain name?
It is used a readable identifier of a website in a network

What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com?
It means that the resource is in a public network

What is the role of the web server
It deals with managing the static resources on a computer network

What is the role of the application server
It manages dynamic information that needs to be generated or accessed from a database

What is the role of the database
It stores data in structured manner to make it accessible

What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website
TCP/IP which is a protocol that defines how data is transferred

ISSUES OF THE ONE SERVER INFRASTRUCTURE
1. Making changes to server-side can be tedious since the server needs to be restarted for the changes to be effected
2. SPOF
	(i) OS failure- if the OS used to run the server fails then the whole infrastructure crumbles.
	(ii) Networking issues - if there are issues with the connectivity then the comminuication is rendered useless

